        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36627",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Moving to other component because Zend_Validate can not affect how Zend_Form creates the validators.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-02T05:30:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-02T05:30:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36733",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maxq",
                        "name": "maxq",
                        "displayName": "Max Kuklin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem in the method addValidators class Zend_Form_Element.\r\n\r\nAn error occurs if you declare validator as follows:\r\n{code}elements.myfield.options.validators.myname = MyValidator{code}\r\nbut not so:\r\n{code}elements.myfield.options.validators.myname.validator = MyValidator{code}\r\n\r\nIn this case, the executable code that does not look at the key array, and takes the parameters in order.\r\n\r\n\r\nTo fix this, for example, can be before the line 1157 in file Zend\/Form\/Element.php:\r\n{code}if (isset($validatorInfo['validator'])) ({code}\r\nadd the following code:\r\n{code}if (!isset($validatorInfo['validator']) && (isset($validatorInfo['breakChainOnFailure']) || isset($validatorInfo['options'])) && \tis_string($validatorInfo[0]))\r\n{\r\n\t$validatorInfo['validator'] = $validatorInfo[0];\r\n}{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maxq",
                        "name": "maxq",
                        "displayName": "Max Kuklin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-05T08:17:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-05T08:17:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37013",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jpieper",
                        "name": "jpieper",
                        "displayName": "Jan Pieper",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Is this really a bug!? You are using a configuration that is not valid.\r\n\r\n{code}elements.email.options.validators.eem = EmailAddress\r\nelements.email.options.validators.eem.options.messages.emailAddressInvalidFormat = \"my message\"{code}\r\n\r\nThe first line creates an array like this:\r\n\r\n{code}array(\r\n    'elements' => array(\r\n        'email' => array(\r\n            'options' => array(\r\n                'validators' => array(\r\n                    'eem' => 'EmailAddress'\r\n                )\r\n            )\r\n        )\r\n    )\r\n){code}\r\n\r\nThe second line needs key \"eem\" to be an array but it isn't. So I don't think this is a bug. I think you need to correct your configuration.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jpieper",
                        "name": "jpieper",
                        "displayName": "Jan Pieper",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-17T23:44:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-17T23:44:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37015",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maxq",
                        "name": "maxq",
                        "displayName": "Max Kuklin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "*Jan Pieper*\r\nYou're right, I described the cause of this problem in the comment above.\r\nThis is not a bug. But you can add at least correct the error message.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maxq",
                        "name": "maxq",
                        "displayName": "Max Kuklin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-18T00:02:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-18T00:02:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37032",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You need to use the following format:\r\n{code}\r\nelements.email.options.validators.eem.validator = \"EmailAddress\"\r\n{code}\r\nNote the \"validator\" key - this is necessary when passing validators via configuration, and is the _documented_ method for configuring element validators (see [the element config section of the manual|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.form.elements.html#zend.form.elements.config]).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-18T06:05:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-18T06:05:16.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
